r: After the Gospel, a homily may follow.
r: The following is then sung or said.
st: the anthem

l:b: Man born of woman has but a short time to live,
l:b: and is full of misery.
l:b: He springs up, and is cut down like a flower;
l:b: he flees like a shadow,
l:b: and never continues the same.
br:
l:b: In the midst of life we are in death:
l:b: of whom do we seek strength,
l:b: but you, O Lord,
l:b: who for our sins are justly displeased?
br:
l:b: Yet, O Lord God most holy,
l:b: O Lord most mighty,
l:b: O holy and most merciful Savior,
l:b: deliver us not into the pains of eternal death.
br:
l:b: You know, O Lord, the secrets of our hearts;
l:b: shut not your ears to our prayer;
l:b: but spare us, Lord most holy,
l:b: O God most mighty,
l:b: O holy and merciful Savior,
l:b: most worthy Judge eternal,
l:b: do not let us, in this our final hour,
l:b: through the pain of death, fall away from you.

